Actions
This procedure assumes the data drive is F: drive and the transaction log drive is G: drive.
This also assumes that the transaction log files for the MASTER, MODEL & MSDB files are located on the F: drive.

Determine when the files went missing by looking in the Application Event Log.

Change the browse time in Networker(with the help of storage team) to some time just before the deletion occurred.

Select the folders to be recovered and recover

This will just recreated the directory structure and associated permissions.

Start the SQL Server Service

This will recreate the templog.ldf file.

Start the SQL Agent service

Log into SQL Server Management Studio. The user databases will need to be recovered.

Using Networker User for SQL Server recover the user databases.
